                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12922AqbaEgziScribe">ʿAqba ʾƎgziʾ</persName> (s. Additio 2)<date notBefore="1700" notAfter="1800">18th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; name of the protagonist; names of the
                           donors; a few lines (alternating with black lines) in the incipit page of
                           Texts I-II; incipits of miracles; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#">ff. 43r, 53r, 74r: </locus>
                        <desc>Crosses</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#102r">f. 102r</locus>
                           <desc type="Record">: Record concerning a qes gabaz (?). </desc><q xml:lang="gez">ገበዝ፡ ቄስ፡ ሐጐስ፡ ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡ መአጐ፡
                              የጊወርጊስ፡ እና፡ የአማኑኤል፡ ታቦታ[sic]፡ መአጐ፡ ክቡራት፡</q>
                           
                           <note> Written by a recent hand in blue pen ink, in the upper part of the
                              folio. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#103va">f. 103va</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Donation note.  </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘአጽሐፈታ፡ በንዋያ፡ ወወሀበታ፡
                              ለመቅደስ፡&lt;…&gt; {አማኑኤል}፡ ከመ፡ ትኵና፡ መርሃ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ምስለ፡ ጸሐፊሃ፡ ዓቅበ፡
                              እግዚእ። ዘሠረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ እግዚአብሔር። <foreign xml:lang="en">
                                 She made the book be written with
                                 her own money and she donated it to the church of ʾAmmānuʾel so that
                                 it might be for her the guide to the Kingdom of Heaven, along with its
                                 scribe <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12922AqbaEgziScribe">ʿAqba ʾƎgziʾ</persName>. The one who steals it or scratches out (its
                                 text), let him be excommunicated by the authority of God.</foreign></q>
                           
                           <note> The note does not mention any personal name. The name of the
                              commissioner and donor (<persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12923ZahalaytMaryam">Zaḫǝlayt/Zaḫalayt Māryām</persName>) is mentioned in the
                              previous folio (103rb), in the supplication note. The note mentions
                              the scribe <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12922AqbaEgziScribe">ʿAqba ʾƎgziʾ</persName>. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc type="GuestText"> <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: Note on <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4306GabraMa">Gabra Manfas
                           Qǝddus</persName>, written in thin pen:<q xml:lang="gez"> ዘመጽሐፍ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ኮከብ፡ ክቡር: ገርማዊ፡ ጸሐየ፡
                           ጽድቅ፡…</q></desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#103va">103va</locus>: Short recent ownership
                           note written in blue pen ink interlineally, next to the supplication
                           formula: <q xml:lang="gez">ዝመጽሀፈ፡ ደቦተ፡ [sic]፡ ጊወረጊስ፡ መአጐ</q>፡</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc type="DonationNote"><locus target="#105r">105r</locus>: Note on the donation written in a crude writing: <q xml:lang="gez">ዝመጽሐፍ፡
                           ዝታቦት፡ ጅዎርገስ፡ መአጎ፡ ና፡ ዝታቦተ፡ ጸሐ[…]…</q></desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc>Pen trials are scattered in the
                           whole codex, especially on <locus target="#1rv">1rv</locus>, 2rv,
                           105rv.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5"><desc>Crude drawings in pencil on <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc type="findingAid">The Vita is divided into monthly readings, from
                              Ṭǝrr (<locus target="#10ra">fol. 10ra</locus>) to Maggābit (written
                              twice: fols. 61ra, 66vb), with the name of months crudely written by a
                              recent hand(s) in the upper margin of folios.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
